Ghostwriter Ghost: Hey, do you think I should start writing again?
Ghostwriter Ghost: No one will read it but ghosts, of course, but...I miss writing.
Ghostwriter Ghost: Sometimes I forget why I became a writer in the first place - it wasn't for money, or fame, or recognition, even if that's what I died wishing for.
Ghostwriter Ghost: I just wanted to write, and for someone to read my work, and feel touched.
<<emotionChange None Flowers>>
Ghostwriter Ghost: And - people did, right? Lots of people! Even if it wasn't my name.
Ghostwriter Ghost: Maybe that's enough.
Ghostwriter Ghost: Maybe, now that I can write under my own name, I'll feel like it's enough.
<<emotionChange None>>
Ghostwriter Ghost: I owe a lot to you for listening to me talk. It might not seem like much to you, but it helped me a bunch.
Ghostwriter Ghost: I think it's time I let myself be happy with what I've accomplished.
<<setCam "Main Camera">>
